  "title": "Primavera Project Planning Engineer | Civil Construction",
  "description": "<ul>\n  <li><strong>Role: Planning Engineer [ Civil Construction Industry ]</strong></li>\n  <li><strong>Industry: A1 Main Contractor</strong></li>\n  <li><strong>HQ at Changi Business Park [ Expo MRT ]</strong></li>\n  <li><strong>Mon to Fri, from 8.30am to 5.15pm</strong></li>\n  <li><strong>Salary is $3.500 - $5,000 + Variable Bonus</strong></li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Job Role </strong></p>\n<ol>\n  <li>The Planning Engineer is responsible for all aspects of planning, scheduling, and reporting for construction projects or tender projects. </li>\n  <li>Maintaining continuous communication and coordination with the construction team, including subcontractors. </li>\n  <li>Assist the Senior Planning Engineer and Project Manager in developing strategies, analyzing procurement and installation schedules, monitoring crew performance, and ensuring effective communication channels are maintained.</li>\n</ol>\n<p><strong>Job requirements</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Degree / Diploma in Civil Engineering (Structural preferred) or equivalent</li>\n  <li>Minimum<u><strong> 2 completed construction project cycle </strong></u>experience </li>\n  <li>Hands-on experience with <u><strong>Primavera </strong></u>for (1-3 years’ experience)</li>\n</ul>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><strong>Job description </strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Prepares Primavera P6, to monitor the progress and substantiate time and cost entitlements.</li>\n  <li>Prepares contract programmes, including high level summary programmes for presentation purposes.</li>\n  <li>Reviews contract conditions so as to highlight onerous provisions, conflicts and discrepancies and to propose recommendations to mitigate risks.</li>\n  <li>Monitors the progress of the construction programme and determines the delay events and their impacts.</li>\n  <li>Assist with the preparation of Extension of Time (EOT) claims, including presentations to clients.</li>\n  <li>Prepares progress reports and progress audits, including S-Curves, progress trackers and programming health checks.</li>\n  <li>Prepares detailed commissioning programmes.</li>\n  <li>Prepares recovery programmes and presentations summarising key recovery strategies.</li>\n  <li>Prepares baseline schedule which includes resource loading and cost loading.</li>\n  <li>Provides advice on post-contract claims, reviews, disputes, and litigation on programming.</li>\n  <li>Other ad-hoc duties by Management assigned from time to time</li>\n</ul>\n<p><br></p>\n<p> #SCR-carson-cheong</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>⭕ Cheong Kar Chun ⭕ Team Manager ⭕ R1980386</p>\n<p>⭕ The Supreme HR Advisory ⭕ 14C7279</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><br></p>",
